Nyeri county yesterday signed a deal with the Housing ministry to build 2,000 houses in Nyeri town. An MoU was signed by Governor Mutahi Kahiga and PS Mwaura Hinga at Kakamega High School on the sidelines of the Fifth Annual Devolution Conference. Nyeri will provide land for the project. Housing is one of the four pillars of the Jubilee administration. The others are food security, manufacturing and affordable healthcare. Earlier, Kahiga met with Safaricom officials over network coverage.